  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rebuilding Young Lives</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The &apos;Rebuilding Young Lives&apos; is a livelihood project that targets orphan children aged 8 to 18 and supports them with provision of livestock, mentoring and shelter. The project had been designed to help child headed households (CHH) and offer them a boost out of extreme poverty, increasing their well-being through the provision of livestock and seeds, shelter, mentorship, training, counselling and healthcare. Our intervention involves a five-tiered support in to improve children&apos;s living conditions, food security, and overall well-being such as health, education, and protection.</narrative>
  </description>
